      { label: 'The Feierabend: Germany\'s Evening Ritual', text: '<em>Feierabend</em> literally means "celebration evening" ‚Äî the cherished transition from work to leisure. Germans gather at beer gardens, Kneipen (pubs), or wine taverns starting around <strong>5‚Äì6 PM</strong>. It\'s social, relaxed, and food-focused. Unlike southern Europe, Germans eat dinner earlier (<strong>6‚Äì8 PM</strong>), so the evening drinking begins after dinner. The Kneipe (neighborhood pub) is the social anchor of German life ‚Äî regulars have their <em>Stammtisch</em> (reserved table). Expect to spend <strong>‚Ç¨10‚Äì20</strong> for a relaxed Feierabend evening.' },
